{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894383589,"sessionID":"ses_2847268ffffew01AouJC1UdUlj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8dbff70015H4llWwxxPgqB8","messageID":"msg_d7b8dacbc00115xhvd4i2LXhac","sessionID":"ses_2847268ffffew01AouJC1UdUlj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4f9f9b8b62754822b7877ab6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-042: Docusaurus 文档站框架\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `docs`  \n6: **Language:** TypeScript  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Docusaurus-based documentation site initialization for agentcube project\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-042.1: Docusaurus Project Initialization\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a Docusaurus v3 project initialized in the `docs/` directory.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Initialize Docusaurus project\n21: - **GIVEN** the agentcube repository root\n22: - **WHEN** the documentation site is initialized\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL create a Docusaurus v3 project in the `docs/` directory\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: TypeScript configuration\n26: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus is initialized\n27: - **WHEN** project is set up\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL use TypeScript for configuration files (`docusaurus.config.ts`)\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Package manager selection\n31: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus CLI runs\n32: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL use the project's existing package manager (npm/pnpm/yarn)\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### REQ-042.2: Docusaurus Configuration\n38: \n39: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `docusaurus.config.ts` configuration file with agentcube branding and settings.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Site title configuration\n42: - **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n43: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n44: - **THEN** `title` SHALL be set to \"agentcube\"\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Site tagline configuration\n47: - **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n48: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n49: - **THEN** `tagline` SHALL describe agentcube's purpose\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Site URL configuration\n52: - **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n53: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n54: - **THEN** `url` SHALL be set to project's documentation URL\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Base URL configuration\n57: - **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n58: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n59: - **THEN** `baseUrl` SHALL be set to `/agentcube/`\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Deployment organization\n62: - **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n63: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n64: - **THEN** `organizationName` SHALL be set to appropriate GitHub org\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Deployment project name\n67: - **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n68: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n69: - **THEN** `projectName` SHALL be set to \"agentcube\"\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Theme configuration\n72: - **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n73: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL configure prism theme for code highlighting\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Navigation bar configuration\n77: - **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n78: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n79: - **THEN** `navbar` SHALL include links to docs, GitHub, and other sections\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Footer configuration\n82: - **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n83: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n84: - **THEN** `footer` SHALL include copyright and relevant links\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### REQ-042.3: Documentation Content Structure\n89: \n90: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a documentation directory structure with initial content.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Docs directory exists\n93: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus project is initialized\n94: - **WHEN** file structure is inspected\n95: - **THEN** `docs/` directory SHALL exist for documentation markdown files\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Introductory documentation\n98: - **GIVEN** `docs/` directory exists\n99: - **WHEN** initial content is created\n100: - **THEN** `docs/intro.md` SHALL provide project introduction\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Getting started documentation\n103: - **GIVEN** `docs/` directory exists\n104: - **WHEN** initial content is created\n105: - **THEN** `docs/getting-started.md` SHALL provide setup instructions\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Docs sidebar configuration\n108: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus is configured\n109: - **WHEN** sidebar is evaluated\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL define a sidebar with intro and getting-started sections\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ### REQ-042.4: Static Assets\n115: \n116: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `static/` directory for static assets with branding.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Static directory exists\n119: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus project is initialized\n120: - **WHEN** file structure is inspected\n121: - **THEN** `static/` directory SHALL exist\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Favicon configuration\n124: - **GIVEN** `static/` directory exists\n125: - **WHEN** assets are added\n126: - **THEN** `static/favicon.ico` SHALL be present\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Logo asset\n129: - **GIVEN** `static/` directory exists\n130: - **WHEN** branding assets are added\n131: - **THEN** `static/img/logo.svg` or `static/img/logo.png` SHALL exist\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Robots.txt\n134: - **GIVEN** `static/` directory exists\n135: - **WHEN** SEO files are added\n136: - **THEN** `static/robots.txt` SHALL be present\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### REQ-042.5: NPM Scripts\n141: \n142: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide NPM scripts in `docs/package.json` for common Docusaurus operations.\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Start script\n145: - **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n146: - **WHEN** scripts are inspected\n147: - **THEN** `start` script SHALL run Docusaurus development server\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Build script\n150: - **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n151: - **WHEN** scripts are inspected\n152: - **THEN** `build` script SHALL generate production build\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Serve script\n155: - **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n156: - **WHEN** scripts are inspected\n157: - **THEN** `serve` script SHALL serve production build locally\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Deploy script\n160: - **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n161: - **WHEN** scripts are inspected\n162: - **THEN** `deploy` script SHALL deploy to GitHub Pages\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ### REQ-042.6: Dependencies\n167: \n168: **Requirement:** The system SHALL specify required Docusaurus dependencies in `package.json`.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Core Docusaurus dependency\n171: - **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n172: - **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n173: - **THEN** `@docusaurus/core` SHALL be listed as dependency (v3.x)\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Preset Classic\n176: - **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n177: - **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n178: - **THEN** `@docusaurus/preset-classic` SHALL be listed as dependency\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: TypeScript support\n181: - **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n182: - **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n183: - **THEN** `@docusaurus/module-type-aliases` and `@docusaurus/tsconfig` SHALL be present\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: React dependencies\n186: - **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n187: - **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n188: - **THEN** `react` and `react-dom` SHALL be listed as dependencies\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ### REQ-042.7: TypeScript Configuration\n193: \n194: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide TypeScript configuration for the docs project.\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: TSConfig file exists\n197: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus project is initialized\n198: - **WHEN** configuration is inspected\n199: - **THEN** `docs/tsconfig.json` SHALL exist\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Docusaurus TSConfig extends\n202: - **GIVEN** `docs/tsconfig.json` exists\n203: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n204: - **THEN** it SHALL extend `@docusaurus/tsconfig`\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Module resolution\n207: - **GIVEN** `docs/tsconfig.json` exists\n208: - **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n209: - **THEN** `moduleResolution` SHALL be set to `bundler` or `node`\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ### REQ-042.8: Git Ignore Configuration\n214: \n215: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `.gitignore` for the docs directory.\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Build output ignored\n218: - **GIVEN** `docs/.gitignore` exists\n219: - **WHEN** gitignore is inspected\n220: - **THEN** `build/` directory SHALL be ignored\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Node modules ignored\n223: - **GIVEN** `docs/.gitignore` exists\n224: - **WHEN** gitignore is inspected\n225: - **THEN** `node_modules/` SHALL be ignored\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Docusaurus cache ignored\n228: - **GIVEN** `docs/.gitignore` exists\n229: - **WHEN** gitignore is inspected\n230: - **THEN** `.docusaurus/` SHALL be ignored\n231: \n232: ---\n233: \n234: ### REQ-042.9: Development Server\n235: \n236: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support running Docusaurus development server for local preview.\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Start development server\n239: - **GIVEN** dependencies are installed\n240: - **WHEN** `npm start` (or equivalent) is executed in `docs/`\n241: - **THEN** Docusaurus dev server SHALL start on `localhost:3000`\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Hot reload\n244: - **GIVEN** dev server is running\n245: - **WHEN** documentation markdown files are modified\n246: - **THEN** changes SHALL be reflected without manual refresh\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Build without errors\n249: - **GIVEN** documentation content exists\n250: - **WHEN** `npm run build` is executed\n251: - **THEN** build SHALL complete without errors\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ### REQ-042.10: README Documentation\n256: \n257: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `docs/README.md` with instructions for working with the documentation site.\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: README exists\n260: - **GIVEN** docs directory is initialized\n261: - **WHEN** file structure is inspected\n262: - **THEN** `docs/README.md` SHALL exist\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Quick start instructions\n265: - **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n266: - **WHEN** content is inspected\n267: - **THEN** it SHALL include commands to start dev server\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: Build instructions\n270: - **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n271: - **WHEN** content is inspected\n272: - **THEN** it SHALL include commands to build production site\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: Deployment instructions\n275: - **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n276: - **WHEN** content is inspected\n277: - **THEN** it SHALL include instructions for deploying to GitHub Pages\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ## Data Types\n282: \n283: ```typescript\n284: // docusaurus.config.ts structure\n285: interface Config {\n286:   title: string;\n287:   tagline: string;\n288:   url: string;\n289:   baseUrl: string;\n290:   organizationName: string;\n291:   projectName: string;\n292:   presets: [\n293:     '@docusaurus/preset-classic',\n294:     {\n295:       docs: DocsOptions;\n296:       blog: false;\n297:       theme: ThemeOptions;\n298:     }\n299:   ];\n300: }\n301: ```\n302: \n303: ```json\n304: // package.json structure\n305: {\n306:   \"name\": \"agentcube-docs\",\n307:   \"version\": \"0.0.0\",\n308:   \"private\": true,\n309:   \"scripts\": {\n310:     \"start\": \"docusaurus start\",\n311:     \"build\": \"docusaurus build\",\n312:     \"serve\": \"docusaurus serve\",\n313:     \"deploy\": \"docusaurus deploy\"\n314:   },\n315:   \"dependencies\": {\n316:     \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.0.0\",\n317:     \"@docusaurus/preset-classic\": \"^3.0.0\",\n318:     \"react\": \"^18.0.0\",\n319:     \"react-dom\": \"^18.0.0\"\n320:   },\n321:   \"devDependencies\": {\n322:     \"@docusaurus/module-type-aliases\": \"^3.0.0\",\n323:     \"@docusaurus/tsconfig\": \"^3.0.0\",\n324:     \"typescript\": \"~5.2.0\"\n325:   }\n326: }\n327: ```\n328: \n329: ---\n330: \n331: ## File Structure\n332: \n333: ```\n334: agentcube/\n335: ├── docs/\n336: │   ├── .gitignore                    # Git ignore for build artifacts\n337: │   ├── README.md                     # Documentation for working with docs\n338: │   ├── package.json                  # NPM dependencies and scripts\n339: │   ├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript configuration\n340: │   ├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Docusaurus site configuration\n341: │   ├── sidebars.ts                   # Documentation sidebar configuration\n342: │   ├── docs/\n343: │   │   ├── intro.md                  # Introduction documentation\n344: │   │   └── getting-started.md        # Getting started guide\n345: │   └── static/\n346: │       ├── favicon.ico               # Site favicon\n347: │       ├── robots.txt                # SEO robots file\n348: │       └── img/\n349: │           └── logo.svg              # Project logo\n350: ```\n351: \n352: ---\n353: \n354: ## NPM Scripts\n355: \n356: | Script | Command | Description |\n357: |--------|---------|-------------|\n358: | `start` | `docusaurus start` | Start development server at localhost:3000 |\n359: | `build` | `docusaurus build` | Generate static build into `build/` |\n360: | `serve` | `docusaurus serve` | Serve production build locally |\n361: | `deploy` | `docusaurus deploy` | Deploy to GitHub Pages |\n362: \n363: ---\n364: \n365: ## Configuration Options\n366: \n367: | Option | Purpose | Default | Overridable |\n368: |--------|---------|---------|-------------|\n369: | `title` | Site title | \"agentcube\" | Yes |\n370: | `tagline` | Site description | \"Documentation\" | Yes |\n371: | `url` | Site URL | \"https://your-docusaurus-site.github.io\" | Yes |\n372: | `baseUrl` | Base URL path | \"/agentcube/\" | Yes |\n373: | `organizationName` | GitHub org | \"volcano-sh\" | Yes |\n374: | `projectName` | GitHub repo | \"agentcube\" | Yes |\n375: | `deploymentBranch` | Deploy branch | \"gh-pages\" | Yes |\n376: \n377: ---\n378: \n379: ## Acceptance Checklist\n380: \n381: - [ ] `docs/` — Directory exists with Docusaurus v3 project\n382: - [ ] `docs/package.json` — Contains required Docusaurus dependencies\n383: - [ ] `docs/package.json` — Contains `start`, `build`, `serve`, `deploy` scripts\n384: - [ ] `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` — TypeScript configuration file exists\n385: - [ ] `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` — Configured with agentcube branding\n386: - [ ] `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` — URL and baseUrl properly set\n387: - [ ] `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` — Navbar configured with links\n388: - [ ] `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` — Footer configured\n389: - [ ] `docs/tsconfig.json` — Extends @docusaurus/tsconfig\n390: - [ ] `docs/sidebars.ts` — Sidebar configuration exists\n391: - [ ] `docs/docs/intro.md` — Introduction documentation exists\n392: - [ ] `docs/docs/getting-started.md` — Getting started guide exists\n393: - [ ] `docs/static/` — Static assets directory exists\n394: - [ ] `docs/static/favicon.ico` — Favicon present\n395: - [ ] `docs/static/img/logo.svg` — Logo asset present\n396: - [ ] `docs/static/robots.txt` — SEO file present\n397: - [ ] `docs/.gitignore` — Ignores `build/`, `node_modules/`, `.docusaurus/`\n398: - [ ] `docs/README.md` — Instructions for working with docs\n399: - [ ] `npm start` — Development server starts successfully\n400: - [ ] `npm run build` — Production build completes without errors\n401: - [ ] Dependencies — All required packages installed\n402: \n403: ---\n404: \n405: ## Open Questions\n406: \n407: 1. Should the documentation site be deployed as part of CI/CD automatically on merge to main?\n408: 2. Should i18n (internationalization) be configured from the start?\n409: 3. Should a blog section be enabled for release announcements?\n410: 4. Should Algolia DocSearch be integrated for search functionality?\n411: 5. Should custom CSS/theming be applied for agentcube branding?\n412: 6. Should versioning (docs versioning) be enabled for multiple releases?\n\n(End of file - total 412 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-042: Docusaurus 文档站框架\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `docs`  \n**Language:** TypeScript  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Docusaurus-based documentation site initialization for agentcube project\n\n**Base Specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-042.1: Docusaurus Project Initialization\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a Docusaurus v3 project initialized in the `docs/` directory.\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize Docusaurus project","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775894383528,"end":1775894383587}}}}
