{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894517030,"sessionID":"ses_2847268ffffew01AouJC1UdUlj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8e1433001Na6Ct0XT4bQSpP","messageID":"msg_d7b8e027b001UoP8mtI9XRqR2S","sessionID":"ses_2847268ffffew01AouJC1UdUlj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_f506ecbe125d4265a25b5c75","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-043/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification — AR-043: 架构设计文档与 API 文档\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `docs`  \n**Language:** Markdown  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Architecture design and API documentation for agentcube project\n\n**Base Specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-043.1: Architecture Documentation Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide an `docs/architecture/` directory with architecture design documentation.\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture directory exists\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube repository root\n- **WHEN** the documentation structure is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/architecture/` directory SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture overview document\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/architecture/overview.md` SHALL provide system architecture overview\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture overview contains system vision\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/overview.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL describe AgentCube's vision as Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture overview contains layered diagram\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/overview.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include ASCII or Mermaid diagram showing Client Layer, API Gateway, Session Routing, Workload Manager, Sandbox Orchestration, and State Storage\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture overview contains component table\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/overview.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include table listing Router, Workload Manager, Sandbox Manager, Store, and PicoD with their responsibilities and tech stack\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture overview contains design decisions\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/overview.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document key design decisions: Kubernetes-native, session affinity, warm pool optimization, and isolated execution\n\n#### Scenario: Core components design document\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/architecture/components.md` SHALL provide detailed component designs\n\n#### Scenario: Router component documentation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/components.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document Router's responsibilities, architecture diagram, and key interfaces\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager component documentation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/components.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document Workload Manager's responsibilities, architecture diagram, and CRD watch mechanism\n\n#### Scenario: Store component documentation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/components.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document Store's responsibilities, Redis/Valkey integration, and architecture\n\n#### Scenario: Data flow design document\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` SHALL describe data flow and request processing\n\n#### Scenario: Session creation flow\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document the session creation flow: Client → Router → Store → Workload Manager → Sandbox Pod\n\n#### Scenario: Request routing flow\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document the request routing flow: Client → Router → Store → Backend URL lookup → Agent Pod\n\n#### Scenario: Session expiration flow\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document the session expiration flow: TTL expires → Redis key deleted → Keyspace notification → Workload Manager deletes sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox lifecycle states\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document sandbox lifecycle states: Pending → Creating → Running → Idle → Terminating → Terminated\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment architecture document\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/architecture/deployment.md` SHALL describe deployment architectures\n\n#### Scenario: Development environment deployment\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/deployment.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document Kind cluster deployment with agentcube-system namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Production environment deployment\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/deployment.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document multi-cluster production deployment with load balancer\n\n#### Scenario: Resource configuration table\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/deployment.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include resource configuration table with CPU/Memory requests and limits for Router, Workload Manager, Redis, and Sandbox Pod\n\n#### Scenario: Security architecture document\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/architecture/security.md` SHALL describe security architecture\n\n#### Scenario: Security boundary diagram\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/security.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include security boundary diagram showing External Network, API Gateway, Internal Network, and Sandbox Pod\n\n#### Scenario: Authentication and authorization\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/security.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document authentication mechanisms: JWT Token, mTLS, RSA Key Pair for PicoD, and Kubernetes RBAC\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox security measures\n- **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/security.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document sandbox security: non-root user, read-only root FS, dropped capabilities, syscall restrictions, namespace isolation, and resource quotas\n\n---\n\n### REQ-043.2: API Documentation Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `docs/api/` directory with API documentation for all core components.\n\n#### Scenario: API directory exists\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube repository root\n- **WHEN** the documentation structure is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/api/` directory SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: API README index\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/api/README.md` SHALL provide API documentation index\n\n#### Scenario: Router API documentation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/api/router.md` SHALL document Router API endpoints\n\n#### Scenario: Router API endpoints documented\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/router.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document endpoints: POST /api/v1/sessions, GET /api/v1/sessions/:sessionID, DELETE /api/v1/sessions/:sessionID\n\n#### Scenario: Router API request/response examples\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/router.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include JSON request/response examples for each endpoint\n\n#### Scenario: Router API client example\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/router.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include Python SDK client usage example\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager API documentation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/api/workload-manager.md` SHALL document Workload Manager API endpoints\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager API endpoints documented\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/workload-manager.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document endpoints: POST /api/v1/workloads, GET /api/v1/workloads/:name, PATCH /api/v1/workloads/:name/scale, DELETE /api/v1/workloads/:name\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager API request/response examples\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/workload-manager.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include JSON request/response examples for each endpoint\n\n#### Scenario: Store API documentation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/api/store.md` SHALL document Store interface\n\n#### Scenario: Store interface methods\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/store.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document interface methods: Set, Get, Delete, Exists, Watch with signatures\n\n#### Scenario: Store event types\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/store.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document Event struct and EventType constants (EventSet, EventDelete)\n\n#### Scenario: Store usage example\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/store.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include Go usage example demonstrating Set, Get, and Watch operations\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox Manager API documentation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` SHALL document Sandbox Manager interface\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox Manager interface methods\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document interface methods: Create, Update, Delete, Get, List with signatures\n\n#### Scenario: WarmPool Manager interface\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document WarmPoolManager interface with Precreate, Acquire, and Refill methods\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox Manager usage example\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include Go usage example demonstrating Create and WarmPool.Acquire operations\n\n#### Scenario: PicoD API documentation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/api/picod.md` SHALL document PicoD API\n\n#### Scenario: PicoD interface methods\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/picod.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document interface methods: Run, Start, RunWithStreaming with signatures\n\n#### Scenario: PicoD Command struct\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/picod.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document Command struct with Path, Args, Env, Dir, and Stdin fields\n\n#### Scenario: PicoD CommandResult struct\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/picod.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document CommandResult struct with ExitCode, Stdout, Stderr, Duration, OOMKilled, and Timeout fields\n\n#### Scenario: PicoD usage example\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/picod.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include Go usage example demonstrating Run command execution\n\n#### Scenario: PicoD HTTP endpoints\n- **GIVEN** `docs/api/picod.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document HTTP endpoints: POST /execute, GET /health with request/response examples\n\n---\n\n### REQ-043.3: Design Specifications Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `docs/design/` directory with coding standards and design specifications.\n\n#### Scenario: Design directory exists\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube repository root\n- **WHEN** the documentation structure is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/design/` directory SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: Coding standards document\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/design/coding-standards.md` SHALL provide coding standards\n\n#### Scenario: Go code formatting standards\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/coding-standards.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL specify: use gofmt/goimports, 120 character line width, tab indentation\n\n#### Scenario: Go naming standards\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/coding-standards.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL specify: lowercase package names, exported identifiers with capital first letter, private identifiers with lowercase first letter\n\n#### Scenario: Error handling standards\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/coding-standards.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL specify: use errors.Wrap for context, lowercase error messages, never ignore errors\n\n#### Scenario: Test standards\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/coding-standards.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL specify: `*_test.go` files, `TestXxx` function names, table-driven tests preferred\n\n#### Scenario: Naming conventions document\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` SHALL provide naming conventions\n\n#### Scenario: CRD naming conventions\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL specify: plural form (agentruntimes, codeinterpreters), short names (ar, ci)\n\n#### Scenario: API Group naming conventions\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL specify format: `<resource>.agentcube.volcano.sh`, versions: v1alpha1, v1beta1, v1\n\n#### Scenario: Environment variable naming\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL specify: AGENTCUBE_ prefix, uppercase (AGENTCUBE_ROUTER_PORT)\n\n#### Scenario: Error handling specification document\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/design/error-handling.md` SHALL provide error handling specification\n\n#### Scenario: Error struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/error-handling.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL document Error struct with Code, Message, and Cause fields\n\n#### Scenario: Error codes table\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/error-handling.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include error codes table: ERR_INVALID_INPUT, ERR_NOT_FOUND, ERR_ALREADY_EXISTS, ERR_TIMEOUT, ERR_INTERNAL\n\n#### Scenario: Error handling pattern\n- **GIVEN** `docs/design/error-handling.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include Go code example: `return nil, errors.Wrap(err, \"failed to create sandbox\")`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-043.4: Documentation Integration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL integrate architecture and API documentation with the AR-042 Docusaurus documentation site.\n\n#### Scenario: Documentation README exists\n- **GIVEN** `docs/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** documentation structure is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/README.md` SHALL exist with documentation guide\n\n#### Scenario: Documentation structure explanation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL explain the relationship between architecture/, api/, design/ directories\n\n#### Scenario: AR-042 and AR-043 relationship\n- **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL explain that AR-043 content serves as