conventions\n\n#### Scenario: Diagram clarity\n- **GIVEN** documentation contains diagrams\n- **WHEN** diagrams are evaluated\n- **THEN** ASCII and Mermaid diagrams SHALL be clear and properly formatted\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```typescript\n// Documentation file structure\ninterface ArchitectureDoc {\n  overview: {\n    vision: string;\n    layers: string[];\n    components: ComponentInfo[];\n    designDecisions: string[];\n  };\n  components: {\n    router: ComponentDesign;\n    workloadManager: ComponentDesign;\n    store: ComponentDesign;\n  };\n  dataFlow: {\n    sessionCreation: FlowStep[];\n    requestRouting: FlowStep[];\n    sessionExpiration: FlowStep[];\n    sandboxLifecycle: string[];\n  };\n  deployment: {\n    development: DeploymentConfig;\n    production: DeploymentConfig;\n    resources: ResourceConfig[];\n  };\n  security: {\n    boundaries: string[];\n    auth: AuthMechanism[];\n    sandboxSecurity: string[];\n  };\n}\n\ninterface APIDoc {\n  router: {\n    endpoints: Endpoint[];\n    clientExample: string;\n  };\n  workloadManager: {\n    endpoints: Endpoint[];\n  };\n  store: {\n    interface: InterfaceMethod[];\n    events: EventType[];\n    usageExample: string;\n  };\n  sandboxManager: {\n    interface: InterfaceMethod[];\n    warmPool: WarmPoolInterface;\n    usageExample: string;\n  };\n  picod: {\n    interface: InterfaceMethod[];\n    structs: StructDefinition[];\n    httpEndpoints: Endpoint[];\n    usageExample: string;\n  };\n}\n\ninterface DesignSpec {\n  codingStandards: {\n    formatting: FormattingRule[];\n    naming: NamingRule[];\n    errorHandling: ErrorHandlingRule[];\n    testing: TestingRule[];\n  };\n  namingConventions: {\n    crd: CRDNaming;\n    apiGroup: string;\n    envVars: string;\n  };\n  errorHandling: {\n    errorStruct: ErrorDefinition;\n    errorCodes: ErrorCode[];\n    pattern: string;\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nagentcube/\n└── docs/\n    ├── README.md                          # Documentation guide and index\n    ├── architecture/                      # Architecture design documentation\n    │   ├── overview.md                    # System architecture overview\n    │   ├── components.md                  # Core component designs\n    │   ├── data-flow.md                   # Data flow and request processing\n    │   ├── deployment.md                  # Deployment architectures\n    │   └── security.md                    # Security architecture\n    ├── api/                               # API documentation\n    │   ├── README.md                      # API documentation index\n    │   ├── router.md                      # Router API reference\n    │   ├── workload-manager.md            # Workload Manager API reference\n    │   ├── store.md                       # Store API reference\n    │   ├── sandbox-manager.md             # Sandbox Manager API reference\n    │   └── picod.md                       # PicoD API reference\n    └── design/                            # Design specifications\n        ├── coding-standards.md            # Go coding standards\n        ├── naming-conventions.md          # Naming conventions\n        └── error-handling.md              # Error handling specification\n```\n\n---\n\n## Documentation Standards\n\n| Element | Standard | Required |\n|---------|----------|----------|\n| File format | Markdown | Yes |\n| Heading style | ATX (#) | Yes |\n| Code blocks | Fenced with language | Yes |\n| Diagrams | ASCII or Mermaid | Yes (where applicable) |\n| API examples | JSON/Go/Python | Yes |\n| Cross-references | Relative links | Yes |\n| Line width | 120 characters max | Recommended |\n\n---\n\n## Content Requirements\n\n### Architecture Documents\n\n| Document | Required Sections | Diagrams | Code Examples |\n|----------|------------------|----------|---------------|\n| overview.md | Vision, Layers, Components, Design Decisions | Layered architecture | No |\n| components.md | Router, Workload Manager, Store | Component architecture | Interface definitions |\n| data-flow.md | Session creation, Routing, Expiration, Lifecycle | Flow diagrams | No |\n| deployment.md | Dev env, Prod env, Resources | Deployment topology | Resource config |\n| security.md | Boundaries, Auth, Sandbox | Security boundary | No |\n\n### API Documents\n\n| Document | Required Sections | Request/Response | Client Examples |\n|----------|------------------|------------------|-----------------|\n| router.md | Endpoints, Examples | JSON | Python SDK |\n| workload-manager.md | Endpoints, Examples | JSON | No |\n| store.md | Interface, Events, Examples | No | Go |\n| sandbox-manager.md | Interface, WarmPool, Examples | No | Go |\n| picod.md | Interface, Structs, HTTP, Examples | JSON | Go |\n\n### Design Documents\n\n| Document | Required Sections | Code Examples |\n|----------|------------------|---------------|\n| coding-standards.md | Formatting, Naming, Errors, Testing | Yes |\n| naming-conventions.md | CRD, API Group, Env Vars | No |\n| error-handling.md | Error struct, Codes, Pattern | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n### Architecture Documentation\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/` — Directory exists\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/overview.md` — Contains system vision and layered architecture diagram\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/overview.md` — Contains component table with responsibilities\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/overview.md` — Documents key design decisions\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/components.md` — Documents Router with interface\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/components.md` — Documents Workload Manager with CRD watch\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/components.md` — Documents Store with Redis integration\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` — Documents session creation flow\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` — Documents request routing flow\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` — Documents session expiration flow\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` — Documents sandbox lifecycle states\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/deployment.md` — Documents Kind development deployment\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/deployment.md` — Documents multi-cluster production deployment\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/deployment.md` — Contains resource configuration table\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/security.md` — Contains security boundary diagram\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/security.md` — Documents authentication mechanisms\n- [ ] `docs/architecture/security.md` — Documents sandbox security measures\n\n### API Documentation\n- [ ] `docs/api/` — Directory exists\n- [ ] `docs/api/README.md` — API documentation index exists\n- [ ] `docs/api/router.md` — Documents POST/GET/DELETE /api/v1/sessions endpoints\n- [ ] `docs/api/router.md` — Contains JSON request/response examples\n- [ ] `docs/api/router.md` — Contains Python SDK usage example\n- [ ] `docs/api/workload-manager.md` — Documents workload CRUD and scale endpoints\n- [ ] `docs/api/workload-manager.md` — Contains JSON request/response examples\n- [ ] `docs/api/store.md` — Documents Store interface with Set/Get/Delete/Exists/Watch\n- [ ] `docs/api/store.md` — Documents Event struct and EventType constants\n- [ ] `docs/api/store.md` — Contains Go usage example\n- [ ] `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` — Documents SandboxManager interface\n- [ ] `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` — Documents WarmPoolManager interface\n- [ ] `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` — Contains Go usage example\n- [ ] `docs/api/picod.md` — Documents PicoD interface with Run/Start/RunWithStreaming\n- [ ] `docs/api/picod.md` — Documents Command and CommandResult structs\n- [ ] `docs/api/picod.md` — Contains Go usage example\n- [ ] `docs/api/picod.md` — Documents POST /execute and GET /health HTTP endpoints\n\n### Design Specifications\n- [ ] `docs/design/` — Directory exists\n- [ ] `docs/design/coding-standards.md` — Documents Go formatting standards\n- [ ] `docs/design/coding-standards.md` — Documents naming standards\n- [ ] `docs/design/coding-standards.md` — Documents error handling standards\n- [ ] `docs/design/coding-standards.md` — Documents testing standards\n- [ ] `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` — Documents CRD naming conventions\n- [ ] `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` — Documents API Group format\n- [ ] `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` — Documents environment variable naming\n- [ ] `docs/design/error-handling.md` — Documents Error struct\n- [ ] `docs/design/error-handling.md` — Documents error codes table\n- [ ] `docs/design/error-handling.md` — Documents error handling pattern\n\n### Documentation Quality\n- [ ] `docs/README.md` — Documentation guide exists\n- [ ] `docs/README.md` — Explains directory structure\n- [ ] `docs/README.md` — Explains AR-042 and AR-043 relationship\n- [ ] Cross-references — Documents link to each other correctly\n- [ ] Terminology — Consistent across all documents\n- [ ] Formatting — Consistent Markdown style\n- [ ] Code examples — Syntactically correct\n- [ ] Diagrams — Clear and properly formatted\n- [ ] API accuracy — Matches actual Go interfaces in pkg/\n- [ ] Architecture accuracy — Matches actual system design\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should API documentation be auto-generated from Go code comments using a tool like swag or gomarkdoc?\n2. Should we integrate with OpenAPI/Swagger for interactive API testing?\n3. Should architecture diagrams use a specific tool (Draw.io, Lucidchart) instead of ASCII/Mermaid?\n4. Should we add versioning to documentation to track changes across releases?\n5. Should we create a separate CHANGELOG.md for documentation updates?\n6. Should API documentation include error response schemas for each endpoint?\n7. Should we add performance benchmarks and SLA documentation?\n8. Should we create troubleshooting guides as part of the architecture documentation?\n9. Should we document migration paths between different versions?\n10. Should we add glossary of terms for new team members?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspace